Subject: [PATCH 312/329] dt-bindings: display: sun4i-drm: document H6 TCON TOP

Allwinner H6 SoC has a cut down version of TCON TOP.

Add binding documentation for it.

Signed-off-by: Icenowy Zheng <icenowy@aosc.io>
---
 .../devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt          | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt
index c1f69a7f4215..11e82235048e 100644
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/display/sunxi/sun4i-drm.txt
@@ -223,13 +223,14 @@ It allows display pipeline to be configured in very different ways:
                  \ [3] TCON-TV1 [1] - TVE1/RGB
 
 Note that both TCON TOP references same physical unit. Both mixers can be
-connected to any TCON.
+connected to any TCON. Units may not exist on a certain SoC.
 
 Required properties:
   - compatible: value must be one of:
     * allwinner,sun8i-r40-tcon-top
+    * allwinner,sun50i-h6-tcon-top
   - reg: base address and size of the memory-mapped region.
-  - clocks: phandle to the clocks feeding the TCON TOP
+  - clocks: phandle to the clocks feeding the TCON TOP, if exist
     * bus: TCON TOP interface clock
     * tcon-tv0: TCON TV0 clock
     * tve0: TVE0 clock
